&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/release/libs/utility/utility.htm#functions_next_prior&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;boost::next() - Boost Utility Library&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.open-std.org/jtc1/sc22/wg21/docs/papers/2007/n2246.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;N2246 2 of the least crazy ideas for the standard library in C++0x&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://wg21.cmeerw.net/lwg/issue2353&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;LWG Issue 2353. &lt;code&gt;std::next&lt;/code&gt; is over-constrained&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
